This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing tasks such as demosaicking and denoising. The use of deep learning architectures also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The mention of convex optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of small datasets and low number of parameters suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
